pnSrMibModule.name: pnSrMibModule

revisions.description: o Add reducer and throughput statistics to the pnSrSysStats group. o Add bytes counts to pnSrAsmStatsTable. o Add bytes counts and bytes-in percentage to pnSrAppStatsTable. o Add pnSrAppAggrStatsTable.
Rev 1.0 Initial version of MIB module PERIBIT-SR-MIB.

pnSrMibModule.contactinfo: Customer Support Peribit Networks, Inc. 2300 Central Expressway Santa Clara, CA 95050 +1 866-PERIBIT support@peribit.com
pnSrMibModule.description: A MIB module containing definitions of managed objects for Peribit Networks' Sequence Reducer family of products.

pnSrConfMib.name: pnSrConfMib
pnSrConfMib.description: Sub-tree for Sequence Reducer MIB conformance statements.

pnSrObjs.name: pnSrObjs
pnSrObjs.description: Sub-tree for Sequence Reducer MIB objects.

pnSrEvents.name: pnSrEvents
pnSrEvents.description: Sub-tree for Sequence Reducer MIB events.

pnSrStatsUpdateTime.name: pnSrStatsUpdateTime
pnSrStatsUpdateTime.description: This is the value of sysUpTime when the SR stats (pnSrSysStats, pnSrAsm, pnSrApp) were last updated. The management station can use this information to tell if it's downloading a consistent set of stats.

pnSrStatsAsmCount.name: pnSrStatsAsmCount
pnSrStatsAsmCount.description: The number of Assemblers this Reducer has had a session with at any time during the last two months.

pnSrStatsAppCount.name: pnSrStatsAppCount
pnSrStatsAppCount.description: The number of applications currently being monitored on this Reducer.

pnSrSysStats.name: pnSrSysStats
pnSrSysStats.description: Sub-tree for Sequence Reducer system statistics.

pnSrSysStatsBytesInAe.name: pnSrSysStatsBytesInAe
pnSrSysStatsBytesInAe.description: Total number of bytes that entered the SR Assembly Engine since the system was started.

pnSrSysStatsBytesOutAe.name: pnSrSysStatsBytesOutAe
pnSrSysStatsBytesOutAe.description: Total number of bytes that exited the SR Assembly Engine after assembly since the system was started.

pnSrSysStatsPktsInAe.name: pnSrSysStatsPktsInAe
pnSrSysStatsPktsInAe.description: Total number of packets that entered the SR Assembly Engine since the system was started.

pnSrSysStatsPktsOutAe.name: pnSrSysStatsPktsOutAe
pnSrSysStatsPktsOutAe.description: Total number of packets that exited the SR Assembly Engine after assembly since the system was started.

pnSrSysStatsBytesOutOob.name: pnSrSysStatsBytesOutOob
pnSrSysStatsBytesOutOob.description: Total number of out-of-band bytes sent to the control channel since the system was started.

pnSrSysStatsBytesPtNoAe.name: pnSrSysStatsBytesPtNoAe
pnSrSysStatsBytesPtNoAe.description: Total number of bytes that passed through the SR Reduction Engine because there was no corresponding Assembly Engine SR, since the system was started.

pnSrSysStatsPktsPtNoAe.name: pnSrSysStatsPktsPtNoAe
pnSrSysStatsPktsPtNoAe.description: Total number of packets that passed through the SR Reduction Engine because there was no corresponding Assembly Engine SR, since the system was started.

pnSrSysStatsBytesPtFilter.name: pnSrSysStatsBytesPtFilter
pnSrSysStatsBytesPtFilter.description: Total number of bytes that passed through the SR Reduction Engine due to a manually configured filter (such as an application filter), since the system was started.

pnSrSysStatsPktsPtFilter.name: pnSrSysStatsPktsPtFilter
pnSrSysStatsPktsPtFilter.description: Total number of packets that passed through the SR Reduction Engine due to a manually configured filter (such as an application filter), since the system was started.

pnSrSysStatsBytesOfPt.name: pnSrSysStatsBytesOfPt
pnSrSysStatsBytesOfPt.description: Total number of bytes that passed through the SR Reduction Engine due to device buffer overflow, since the system was started.

pnSrSysStatsPktsOfPt.name: pnSrSysStatsPktsOfPt
pnSrSysStatsPktsOfPt.description: Total number of packets that passed through the SR Reduction Engine due to device buffer overflow, since the system was started.

pnSrSysStatsBytesTpIn.name: pnSrSysStatsBytesTpIn
pnSrSysStatsBytesTpIn.description: The number of bytes into the SR Reduction Engine at the peak five-second interval of data input, since the system was started.

pnSrSysStatsPktsTpIn.name: pnSrSysStatsPktsTpIn
pnSrSysStatsPktsTpIn.description: The number of packets into the SR Reduction Engine at the peak five-second interval of data input, since the system was started.

pnSrSysStatsBytesTpOut.name: pnSrSysStatsBytesTpOut
pnSrSysStatsBytesTpOut.description: The number of bytes out of the SR Reduction Engine at the peak five-second interval of data input, since the system was started.

pnSrSysStatsPktsTpOut.name: pnSrSysStatsPktsTpOut
pnSrSysStatsPktsTpOut.description: The number of packets out of the SR Reduction Engine at the peak five-second interval of data input, since the system was started.

pnSrSysStatsBytesTpPt.name: pnSrSysStatsBytesTpPt
pnSrSysStatsBytesTpPt.description: The number of bytes that passed through the SR Reduction Engine at the peak five-second interval of data input, since the system was started.

pnSrSysStatsPktsTpPt.name: pnSrSysStatsPktsTpPt
pnSrSysStatsPktsTpPt.description: The number of packets that passed through the SR Reduction Engine at the peak five-second interval of data input, since the system was started.

pnSrSysStatsPeakRdn.name: pnSrSysStatsPeakRdn
pnSrSysStatsPeakRdn.description: The maximum data reduction rate for a five second interval in the last minute. The value returned is (percentage * 1000). Applications should divide the returned value by 1000.

pnSrSysStatsThruputIn.name: pnSrSysStatsThruputIn
pnSrSysStatsThruputIn.description: Average throughput of incoming data in Kbps since the system was started.

pnSrSysStatsThruputOut.name: pnSrSysStatsThruputOut
pnSrSysStatsThruputOut.description: Average throughput of outgoing data in Kbps since the system was started.

pnSrSysStatsBytesInRe.name: pnSrSysStatsBytesInRe
pnSrSysStatsBytesInRe.description: Total number of bytes that entered the SR Reduction Engine since the system was started.

pnSrSysStatsBytesOutRe.name: pnSrSysStatsBytesOutRe
pnSrSysStatsBytesOutRe.description: Total number of bytes that exited the SR Reduction Engine after reduction since the system was started.

pnSrSysStatsPktsInRe.name: pnSrSysStatsPktsInRe
pnSrSysStatsPktsInRe.description: Total number of packets that entered the SR Reduction Engine since the system was started.

pnSrSysStatsPktsOutRe.name: pnSrSysStatsPktsOutRe
pnSrSysStatsPktsOutRe.description: Total number of packets that exited the SR Reduction Engine after reduction since the system was started.

pnSrAsm.name: pnSrAsm
pnSrAsm.description: Information maintained by a Reducer for each Assembler it has a session with.

pnSrAsmTable.name: pnSrAsmTable
pnSrAsmTable.description: List of Assemblers the Reducer has sessions with.

pnSrAsmIpAddress.name: pnSrAsmIpAddress
pnSrAsmIpAddress.description: The IP address of the Assembler.

pnSrAsmStatsTable.name: pnSrAsmStatsTable
pnSrAsmStatsTable.description: Statistics maintained by a Reducer for each Assembler it has a session with.

pnSrAsmStatsPktsIn.name: pnSrAsmStatsPktsIn
pnSrAsmStatsPktsIn.description: The total number of packets into this SR, since the system was started, that were identified for reduction and addressed to the SR whose IP address is in the row in pnSrAsmTable that matches this row.

pnSrAsmStatsPktsOut.name: pnSrAsmStatsPktsOut
pnSrAsmStatsPktsOut.description: The total number of packets out of this SR, since the system was started, that were identified for reduction and addressed to the SR whose IP address is in the row in pnSrAsmTable that matches this row.

pnSrAsmStatsBytesIn.name: pnSrAsmStatsBytesIn
pnSrAsmStatsBytesIn.description: The total number of bytes into this SR, since the system was started, that were identified for reduction and addressed to the SR whose IP address is in the row in pnSrAsmTable that matches this row.

pnSrAsmStatsBytesOut.name: pnSrAsmStatsBytesOut
pnSrAsmStatsBytesOut.description: The total number of bytes out of this SR, since the system was started, that were identified for reduction and addressed to the SR whose IP address is in the row in pnSrAsmTable that matches this row.

pnSrApp.name: pnSrApp
pnSrApp.description: Information maintained by a Reducer for each application that is monitored.

pnSrAppAppName.name: pnSrAppAppName
pnSrAppAppName.description: The name of the application from which the data was received (e.g., FTP, HTTP, Lotus Notes).

pnSrAppStatsTable.name: pnSrAppStatsTable
pnSrAppStatsTable.description: Statistics maintained by a Reducer for each application that is monitored.

pnSrAppStatsEntry.name: pnSrAppStatsEntry
pnSrAppStatsEntry.description: A row in pnSrAppStatsTable. Note that the indices are from pnSrAsmTable and pnSrAppTable. For each Assembler this reducer has a session with (indexed by pnSrAsmIndex), statistics are maintained for each application that is monitored (indexed by pnSrAppIndex).

pnSrAppStatsBytesIn.name: pnSrAppStatsBytesIn
pnSrAppStatsBytesIn.description: The total number of bytes into the SR, since the system was started, that were identified for reduction, and addressed to the SR whose IP address is in the row in pnSrAsmTable that matches the index pnSrAsmIndex, and that was received from the application whose name is in the row in pnSrAppTable that matches the index pnSrAppIndex.

pnSrAppStatsBytesOut.name: pnSrAppStatsBytesOut
pnSrAppStatsBytesOut.description: The total number of bytes out of the SR, since the system was started, that were identified for reduction, and addressed to the SR whose IP address is in the row in pnSrAsmTable that matches the index pnSrAsmIndex, and that was received from the application whose name is in the row in pnSrAppTable.

pnSrAppStatsBytesInPercent.name: pnSrAppStatsBytesInPercent
pnSrAppStatsBytesInPercent.description: The percentage of the bytes in for this application over the total bytes into the SR, since the system was started, that were identified for reduction, and addressed to the SR whose IP address is in the row in pnSrAsmTable that matches the index pnSrAsmIndex, and that was received from the application whose name is in the row in pnSrAppTable that matches the index pnSrAppIndex. The value returned is (percentage * 1000). Applications should divide the returned value by 1000.

pnSrAppStatsAppName.name: pnSrAppStatsAppName
pnSrAppStatsAppName.description: The name of the application from which the data was received (e.g., FTP, HTTP, Lotus Notes). NOTE: This object is here even though it's also in pnSrAppTable. This is for the convenience of network monitoring tools that require all columns to be from the same table.

pnSrAppAggrStatsTable.name: pnSrAppAggrStatsTable
pnSrAppAggrStatsTable.description: Aggregate statistics maintained by a Reducer for each application that is monitored. These statistics apply to the reducer as a whole and are summed over all assembler sessions maintained by the reducer.

pnSrAppAggrStatsBytesInRe.name: pnSrAppAggrStatsBytesInRe
pnSrAppAggrStatsBytesInRe.description: Total number of bytes that entered the SR Reduction Engine for this application since the system was started.

pnSrAppAggrStatsBytesOutRe.name: pnSrAppAggrStatsBytesOutRe
pnSrAppAggrStatsBytesOutRe.description: Total number of bytes that exited the SR Reduction Engine after reduction for this application since the system was started.

pnSrAppAggrStatsBytesInPercent.name: pnSrAppAggrStatsBytesInPercent
pnSrAppAggrStatsBytesInPercent.description: The percentage of the bytes in for this application over the total bytes into the SR Reduction Engine. The value returned is (percentage * 1000). Applications should divide the returned value by 1000.

pnSrBurstStats.name: pnSrBurstStats
pnSrBurstStats.description: Sub-tree for Sequence Reducer system statistics.

pnSrBurstStatsStartTime.name: pnSrBurstStatsStartTime
pnSrBurstStatsStartTime.description: The start of the minute in seconds since midnight (00:00:00), January 1, 1970, UTC over which the burst stats apply.

pnSrBurstStatsBpsIn.name: pnSrBurstStatsBpsIn
pnSrBurstStatsBpsIn.description: Burst bits per second into reduction engine for the past minute.

pnSrBurstStatsBpsOut.name: pnSrBurstStatsBpsOut
pnSrBurstStatsBpsOut.description: Burst bits per second out of reduction engine for the past minute.

pnSrBurstStatsBpsPt.name: pnSrBurstStatsBpsPt
pnSrBurstStatsBpsPt.description: Burst pass-through bits per second for the past minute.

pnSrEventObjs.name: pnSrEventObjs
pnSrEventObjs.description: Branch for objects meant only to be sent in event varbinds.

pnSrEventEventsV2.name: pnSrEventEventsV2
pnSrEventEventsV2.description: Branch for SNMPv2 events. The OIDs for SNMPv2 events should have a zero as the next-to-last sub-identifier (as specified in RFC1902).

pnSrEventReducerBufferOverflow.name: pnSrEventReducerBufferOverflow
pnSrEventReducerBufferOverflow.description: The reducer's input buffer is approaching full capacity.

pnSrEventReducerSessionClosed.name: pnSrEventReducerSessionClosed
pnSrEventReducerSessionClosed.description: The reducer's session to the device described in pnCommonEventDescr was terminated.

pnSrEventAssemblerSessionClosed.name: pnSrEventAssemblerSessionClosed
pnSrEventAssemblerSessionClosed.description: The assembler's session to the device described in pnCommonEventDescr was terminated.

pnSrEventReducerSessionOpened.name: pnSrEventReducerSessionOpened
pnSrEventReducerSessionOpened.description: The reducer's session to the device described in pnCommonEventDescr was opened.

pnSrEventAssemblerSessionOpened.name: pnSrEventAssemblerSessionOpened
pnSrEventAssemblerSessionOpened.description: The assembler's session to the device described in pnCommonEventDescr was opened.

pnSrEventPrimaryRegServerUnreachable.name: pnSrEventPrimaryRegServerUnreachable
pnSrEventPrimaryRegServerUnreachable.description: The primary registration server is currently unreachable.

pnSrEventSecondaryRegServerUnreachable.name: pnSrEventSecondaryRegServerUnreachable
pnSrEventSecondaryRegServerUnreachable.description: The secondary registration server is currently unreachable.

pnSrEventMultiNodeMasterUp.name: pnSrEventMultiNodeMasterUp
pnSrEventMultiNodeMasterUp.description: The system designated as the 'master' of a multi-node came up. This notification is generated by the system that's designated as the 'master' of the multi-node. Note that the corresponding Down notification is generated by the designated 'master-backup' of the same multi-node.

pnSrEventMultiNodeMasterDown.name: pnSrEventMultiNodeMasterDown
pnSrEventMultiNodeMasterDown.description: The system designated as the 'master' of a multi-node is currently down. This notification is generated by the system that's designated as the 'master-backup' of the same multi-node. Note that the corresponding Up notification is generated by the designated 'master' of the same multi-node.

pnSrEventMultiNodeLastUp.name: pnSrEventMultiNodeLastUp
pnSrEventMultiNodeLastUp.description: The system designated as the 'last-node' of a multi-node came up. This notification is generated by the system that's designated as the 'last-node' of the multi-node. Note that the corresponding Down notification is generated by the designated 'master' of the same multi-node.

pnSrEventMultiNodeLastDown.name: pnSrEventMultiNodeLastDown
pnSrEventMultiNodeLastDown.description: The system designated as the 'last-node' of a multi-node is currently down. This notification is generated by the system that's designated as the 'master' of the same multi-node. Note that the corresponding Up notification is generated by the designated 'last-node' of the same multi-node.

pnSrEventPrimaryDownBackupEngaged.name: pnSrEventPrimaryDownBackupEngaged
pnSrEventPrimaryDownBackupEngaged.description: The system designated as the 'primary' is currently unreachable. This notification is generated by the system that's designated as the 'backup' device. The backup device is engaged for the primary device.

pnSrEventPrimaryDownBackupEngageFailed.name: pnSrEventPrimaryDownBackupEngageFailed
pnSrEventPrimaryDownBackupEngageFailed.description: The system designated as the 'primary' is currently unreachable. This notification is generated by the system that's designated as the 'backup' device. The backup device failed to engage for the primary device.

pnSrEventPrimaryUpBackupDisengaged.name: pnSrEventPrimaryUpBackupDisengaged
pnSrEventPrimaryUpBackupDisengaged.description: The system designated as the 'primary' is currently reachable. This notification is generated by the system that's designated as the 'backup' device. The backup device has disengaged itself.

pnSrEventMultiPathStatusChange.name: pnSrEventMultiPathStatusChange
pnSrEventMultiPathStatusChange.description: The status of the primary or secondary path to another multi-path enabled system changed. The path became inactive or failed after previously being active or vice versa. This might have caused traffic designated to flow over this path to be switched from or to this path.

pnSrEventDiskFailure.name: pnSrEventDiskFailure
pnSrEventDiskFailure.description: A hard disk failed on the system. The system was rebooted, and will now operate without the downed disk, at a degraded performance. Dictionary accumulated until this point was lost.
